If she lays 16 eggs and uses 7, then the remainder would be 16 - 7 = 9 eggs. Then she sells those 9 eggs at $2 each. So 9 times $2 is 18 dollars. Therefore, she makes $18 every day.

Wait, but let me check again. The problem says she eats three for breakfast every morning and bakes muffins for her friends every day with four. So maybe the "with four" refers to the number of eggs used in baking? So, maybe she uses three eggs for breakfast and four eggs for baking, totaling seven. So 16 - 7 = 9. Then 9 * 2 = 18. That seems right. So the answer is 18 dollars. Let me make sure I didn't miss anything.

